  "text": "The xDS v3 transport protocol implementation in envoyproxy/envoy is located in the `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/` directory and supporting files in `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/`.\n\n## Core Components:\n\n### 1. Unified XdsMux Template (grpc_mux_impl.h/cc)\nThe template class `GrpcMuxImpl<S, F, RQ, RS>` in `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h` is the unified transport protocol implementation supporting both State-of-the-World (SotW) and Delta variants. It is parameterized by:\n- `S`: SubscriptionState type (SotwSubscriptionState or DeltaSubscriptionState)\n- `F`: SubscriptionStateFactory type (SotwSubscriptionStateFactory or DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory)\n- `RQ`: Request type (DiscoveryRequest or DeltaDiscoveryRequest)\n- `RS`: Response type (DiscoveryResponse or DeltaDiscoveryResponse)\n\nTemplate instantiations in `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.cc` create two concrete specializations:\n- `template class GrpcMuxImpl<DeltaSubscriptionState, DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory, DeltaDiscoveryRequest, DeltaDiscoveryResponse>`\n- `template class GrpcMuxImpl<SotwSubscriptionState, SotwSubscriptionStateFactory, DiscoveryRequest, DiscoveryResponse>`\n\n### 2. Concrete GrpcMux Implementations\n`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h` defines:\n- `GrpcMuxDelta`: Delta xDS implementation inheriting from GrpcMuxImpl with DeltaSubscriptionState\n- `GrpcMuxSotw`: SotW implementation inheriting from GrpcMuxImpl with SotwSubscriptionState\n\n### 3. Subscription State Variants\n`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h` implements SotwSubscriptionState for state-of-the-world protocol tracking with version and nonce management for full state exchange.\n\n`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.h` implements DeltaSubscriptionState for delta protocol tracking with per-resource version tracking and incremental updates.\n\nBoth inherit from `BaseSubscriptionState<RS, RQ>` defined in `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/subscription_state.h`.\n\n### 4. GrpcSubscriptionImpl Adapter\n`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h/cc` provides the `GrpcSubscriptionImpl` adapter that bridges between the typed Subscription interface and the untyped GrpcMux interface. It handles per-xDS API statistics, logging, and lifecycle management.\n\n### 5. Factory Selection Pattern\n`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_factory.h/cc` implements the factory pattern:\n- `GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory::create()` selects between legacy GrpcMuxImpl and unified `GrpcMuxSotw` based on the runtime feature flag `envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux`\n- `DeltaGrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory::create()` similarly selects between `NewGrpcMuxImpl` (legacy) and unified `GrpcMuxDelta`\n\nBoth factories wrap the selected GrpcMux with a `GrpcSubscriptionImpl` adapter.\n\n## Summary\nThe xDS v3 transport protocol is implemented through a unified template-based architecture in the XdsMux namespace that supports both SotW and Delta variants through template specialization and factory selection, providing clean separation of concerns between protocol state management, transport mechanics, and subscription adaptation."
}

